@gerkey : The hand cameras are generated at 30Hz and there is no way to request them at lower rates. [I did ask on May 16th](#!/osrf/drcsim/issue/272/setting-sensor-rates). What about generating these at lower rates? It would only be a matter of changing the urdf for the hands.

The laser generates very little data relative to the cameras and we only need the cameras a low rates.

And as Jesper said, we could only have run at realtime if we could give every teammember 3 expensive desktops. We use both fc1 and fc2.
